## Classe principale

```java
package com.example.demo;

import org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;
import org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.SpringBootApplication;

@SpringBootApplication
public class DemoApplication {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(DemoApplication.class, args);
    }
}
```

---

## Classe `Todo`

Cette classe représente la réponse JSON de l’API.

```java
package com.example.demo.test;

public class Todo {

    private Integer userId;
    private Integer id;
    private String title;
    private Boolean completed;

    public Integer getUserId() {
        return userId;
    }

    public void setUserId(Integer userId) {
        this.userId = userId;
    }

    public Integer getId() {
        return id;
    }

    public void setId(Integer id) {
        this.id = id;
    }

    public String getTitle() {
        return title;
    }

    public void setTitle(String title) {
        this.title = title;
    }

    public Boolean getCompleted() {
        return completed;
    }

    public void setCompleted(Boolean completed) {
        this.completed = completed;
    }
}
```

---

## `TestController`

```java
package com.example.demo.test;

import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;
import org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate;

@RestController
public class TestController {

    @GetMapping("/test/public-api")
    public Todo callPublicApi() {
        RestTemplate restTemplate = new RestTemplate();
        String url = "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos/1";
        return restTemplate.getForObject(url, Todo.class);
    }
}
```

---

## Explication

Quand on appelle :

```text
GET /test/public-api
```

le controller :

- crée un `RestTemplate`
- appelle l’URL publique
- convertit automatiquement le JSON en objet `Todo`
- renvoie cet objet en JSON

