## Variante encore plus simple sans classe Java

Si tu veux juste tester rapidement, tu peux récupérer un `String`.

```java
package com.example.demo.test;

import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.GetMapping;
import org.springframework.web.bind.annotation.RestController;
import org.springframework.web.client.RestTemplate;

@RestController
public class TestController {

    @GetMapping("/test/public-api-string")
    public String callPublicApiAsString() {
        RestTemplate restTemplate = new RestTemplate();
        String url = "https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos/1";
        return restTemplate.getForObject(url, String.class);
    }
}
```

---

## URL à tester

```text
http://localhost:3000/test/public-api-string
```

---

## Réponse attendue

```json
{"userId":1,"id":1,"title":"delectus aut autem","completed":false}
```

